def min_moves_to_divisible_by_25(n: str) -> int:
    s = n[::-1]
    t = len(s)

    def g(c, i=0):
        return s.find(str(c), i) + 1 or 50
    (i, f) = (g(0), g(5))
    j = min(g(0, i), f)
    m = i + j - (j < i)
    j = min(g(2), g(7))
    l = f + j + (j < f)
    if f == t:
        i = t - 1
        while s[i - 1] == '0':
            l += 1
            i -= 1
    m = min(m, l)
    return (-1, m - 3)[m < 40]
